sequenceDiagram
    participant U as Content Creator
    participant WA as Web Application
    participant LO as LibreOffice
    participant EMB as Azure OpenAI<br/>(Embeddings)
    participant LLM as Azure OpenAI<br/>(GPT-4.1)
    participant VS as In-Memory<br/>Vector Store
    participant BS as Azure Blob Storage
    participant CDB as Azure Cosmos DB

    Note over U,CDB: UPLOAD & PARSE PHASE

    U->>WA: 1. Upload PowerPoint (.pptx)
    WA->>WA: 2. Validate file<br/>(ZIP header, Content_Types.xml)
    WA->>WA: 3. python-pptx: extract<br/>(title, body, notes, videos)
    WA->>LO: 4. soffice --headless --convert-to pdf
    LO-->>WA: 5. PDF → pdf2image → PNGs

    Note over WA,CDB: PERSIST TO AZURE

    WA->>BS: 6. Upload slide PNGs to<br/>slide-images/{id}/{idx}.png
    WA->>BS: 7. Upload original PPTX to<br/>slide-images/{id}/{file}.pptx

    WA->>CDB: 8. Save presentation metadata<br/>(id, filename, slides[], pptx_url)

    Note over WA,VS: INDEX FOR Q&A

    loop For each slide
        WA->>EMB: 9. embeddings.create(title + body + notes)
        EMB-->>WA: 10. Embedding vector
        WA->>VS: 11. Store {embedding, slide metadata}
    end

    Note over WA,CDB: BACKGROUND TRANSLATION

    WA-->>U: 12. Presentation ready (SAS-signed image URLs)

    loop For each of 9 target languages (async)
        WA->>LLM: 13. Translate all slide notes
        LLM-->>WA: 14. Translated text
        WA->>CDB: 15. Cache in slides[].translated_notes.{lang}
    end
